                                                                                        <a href="https://github.com/knpuniversity/symfony/edit/master/knpu/extra-form-theming/form-type-extension-magic.md" target="_blank" class="btn btn-default btn-circle pull-right js-tooltip" title="Edit on GitHub"><span class="fa fa-pencil"></span></a>
                                                                    <p>The only way to make an option valid for a field is to, well, hack the core class
and add it! For example, since <code>funFact</code> is a <code>TextType</code>, I <em>could</em> - if I were feeling
crazy - open <code>TextType</code>, scroll down, and hack that <code>help</code> option into <code>configureOptions()</code>:</p>
