<p>That's a ridiculous, and yet, fully-functional type extension.</p>
<h2 id="registering-a-type-extension">Registering a Type Extension <a class="headerlink" href="form-type-extension-magic#registering-a-type-extension" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>To tell Symfony about this, you guys can probably guess, we need to register this
as a service. In <code>app/config/services.yml</code>, add a new service: call it
<code>app.form.help_form_extension</code>. Set its class to <code>HelpFormExtension</code> and then I'll
set <code>autowire</code> to true... even though the class doesn't have any constructor arguments,
at least not yet:</p>
