</p>
<p>Then, to actually tell Symfony: "Hey! This is a form type extension!", add a tag,
set to <code>form.type_extension</code>. Also give this an <code>extended_type</code> option. This needs
to match whatever you're returning from <code>getExtendedType()</code>. <code>FormType::class</code>
returns the long string in the <code>use</code> statement, so copy that, and paste it into your
service:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="b3460d4779">
    <div class="meta">
        <div class="actions">
            <span class="fa fa-clipboard js-activate-clipboard" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Copy Code" data-placement="top"></span>
