</p>
<p>That's it team! Temporarily remove the <code>help</code> option from <code>GenusFormType</code>, ya know,
so the page doesn't explode. Then, refresh! OMG, everyone is screaming about
TURTLES! Well, everyone except for the <code>isPublished</code> field, because we're overriding
that <code>help</code> variable at the last possible second: from inside the template.</p>
<h2 id="using-the-option-to-fuel-the-help-variable">Using the Option to Fuel the help Variable <a class="headerlink" href="form-type-extension-magic#using-the-option-to-fuel-the-help-variable" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Finally, uncomment the <code>help</code> option. So, how can we make this a valid option? Go
back to <code>HelpFormExtension</code>, use the "Code"-&gt;"Generate" menu one last time, click
"Override Methods", and select <code>configureOptions()</code>:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="55056e6203">
